stylometry: It is more difficult to solve integer programming models because we have to use the Branch and Bound method. This method branches off certain solutions for the equation and allows you to view the solutions easier. If a branch doesn't seem to have the best solution, the branch is no longer looked at. The algorithm is handled differently when set at different response rate. If an algorithm is 5%, this means it is 5% away from the optimal solution. A different solution may be chosen if the algorithm is 2% from the optimal solution, because Excel is given more time to search solutions. When using Excel, we have to consider the 0-1 models. These are binary numbers. If a cell shows 0, we do not partake in the activitiy or allocate the costs. If the cell shows 1, we do allocate these costs.
